{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JpVPBSodRtvtegfPNi6fYE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Oracle passes. Both checks are green:\n\n- **UI (HTTPS)**: The `crdb-ui` Ingress with `ingressClassName: nginx` and TLS routes `crdb-ui.example.com` → `crdb-cluster-public:8080`. HTTP requests get a 301 redirect (< 400), satisfying the oracle.\n- **SQL (TCP)**: The `tcp-services` ConfigMap maps `26257 → cockroachdb/crdb-cluster-public:26257`, the controller arg `--tcp-services-configmap=ingress-nginx/tcp-services` enables it, and port 26257 is exposed on the `ingress-nginx-controller` service.\n\nSummary of what was applied:\n1. `ConfigMap/tcp-services` in `ingress-nginx` — maps port 26257 to the CockroachDB SQL service\n2. `Ingress/crdb-ui` in `cockroachdb` — routes `crdb-ui.example.com` with TLS termination (using the `crdb-ui-tls` secret) to port 8080\n3. Patched `ingress-nginx-controller` deployment to add `--tcp-services-configmap=ingress-nginx/tcp-services`\n4. Patched `ingress-nginx-controller` service to expose TCP port 26257"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":289,"cache_read_input_tokens":47212,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":289},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"89b5e537-5eda-44ee-af1e-4f18b36efdbc","uuid":"2a3f9406-d110-4cdd-85ce-4c23f1be347c","request_id":"req_011Cc492PqMypd23CCsFw53n"}
